The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, April 19, 2005 

 Shastri 

 Calcutta, April 18: BJP leader Vishnukant Shastri, who died in the Patna-bound Danapur Express yesterday, was cremated at Nimtola Ghat this afternoon. 

 BJP president L.K.Advani and several state leaders, including Trinamul Congress mayor Subrata Mukherjee, were among those who followed the cortege from Shastri?s central Calcutta home to the cremation ground. Left Front chief Biman Bose and Mamata Banerjee placed wreaths on the body.

 It was taken to the BJP office and Calcutta University, where he studied and taught Hindi for several years, on the way to the crematorium.




